President Obama spoke with Prime Minister Stephen Harper of Canada about the Ebola outbreak and the counter-ISIL campaign. They discussed the need for greater international action to combat Ebola and ways that the United States and Canada can collaborate to stop the spread of the virus. They also talked about the progress in the campaign against ISIL and Canada's contributions to the effort, including sending advisors to train Iraqi forces and deploying fighter jets and intelligence assets to support coalition airstrikes in Iraq. The President updated Prime Minister Harper on recent developments and the growing international coalition against ISIL.